comments: Griffin's (BKN) arm is not vertical when it makes contact to Embiid's (PHI) arm which affects his shot attempt in the post.
Harris (PHI) jumps into and makes contact with Durant's (BKN) body after the release, which affects his ability to follow-through on his jump shot attempt.
During the screen, Edwards (BKN) briefly engages and marginal contact occurs as he immediately disengages with Curry (PHI) off-ball.
Griffin (BKN) maintains a legal guarding position with a collapsed forearm to Embiid's (PHI) back as he absorbs the contact in the post.
Griffin (BKN) legally contests Embiid's (PHI) fadeaway jump shot attempt.
Curry (PHI) commits a take foul on Duke Jr. (BKN).
Claxton (BKN) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by Curry (PHI).
Milton (PHI) deflects the pass and Durant (PHI) is legally allowed to regain possession of the loose ball in the backcourt.
Curry (PHI) is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
